@node Installation "Eraser: Installation"

                                  Installation
                                 --------------

- copy the file Eraser.pss from drawer plugins2/ to ArtEffect:plugins2/

- copy Eraser.guide whereever you can retrieve it.

After the next start of ArtEffect2+ the menuentry "Eraser VR..." should be
available in Menu Filter/Other.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Eraser: Requirements"

                                  Requirements
                                 --------------

- the only thing you need is ArtEffect2+

@endnode

@node Usage "Eraser: Usage"

                                     Usage
                                    -------

   The usage is quite easy, after calling the plugin via menu, you will see a
   little window. Please note that I'm using 'mask' as synonym for 'stencil'
   in ArtEffect.

   The GUI is very simple, you can decide to which color the picture should be
   erased to.
   To Foreground- or Backgroundcolor, White or Black.

   Just press Execute to start erasing.

   The mask of the picture is respected and kept unchanged.

@endnode

@node Notes "Eraser: Notes"

                                     Notes
                                    -------


 - Eraser was written on an Amiga 4000 with Cyberstorm MK1 060 and compiled with
   SAS/C 6.58.

 - This PlugIn has no AREXX-Interface and is not localized nor the documentation
   is avaiable in any other language than english (or whatever this is here).
   That may or may not change in the future.

@endnode

